org.apache.ambari.server.state.quicklinksprofile

Class QuickLinksProfile

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.ambari.server.state.quicklinksprofile.QuickLinksProfile

  • public class QuickLinksProfile
extends Object
    A quicklinks profile is essentially a set of quick link filters defined on three levels:
    • global level
    • service level
    • component level (within a service)

    For each link, filters are evaluated bottom up: component level filters take priority to service level filters and service level filters take priority to global filters.

    When a quick link profile is set in Ambari, then each quick link's visibility flag is updated according to the profile before being returned by QuickLinkArtifactResourceProvider.

    When no profile is set, all quick link's visibility flat will be set to true by the provider
